# /etc/sudo.conf -- example registration of the TrustForge sudo policy plugin.
#
# Copy this file to /etc/sudo.conf (or merge the Plugin lines into your
# existing /etc/sudo.conf). sudo reads /etc/sudo.conf at startup; changes
# take effect on the next sudo invocation. Keep a root shell open while
# editing in case of a misconfiguration.
#
# Both lines are required: the policy plugin gates the call, and
# sudoers_io is a stock I/O logging plugin shipped with sudo. If you do
# not want I/O logging you may omit the second line.
#
# Plugins must be installed root-owned, mode 0644 (or stricter), in the
# distribution-specific plugin directory. Common locations:
#   Debian/Ubuntu:  /usr/lib/sudo/
#   Fedora/RHEL:    /usr/libexec/sudo/
#   Alpine:         /usr/lib/sudo/

Plugin sudoers_policy sudo_trustforge.so
Plugin sudoers_io     sudoers.so
